    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-09-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-05-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="261" subtype="editorial-note"
                type="document" xml:id="d261">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>No official record of this informal meeting has been found. At the meeting of the
                    Joint Chiefs of Staff on the following day <persName corresp="#p_MGC1"
                        >Marshall</persName> referred to his dinner conversation with <persName
                        corresp="#p_CC2">Churchill</persName> and indicated that the latter had
                    discussed operations in the Dodecanese, the capture of Rhodes, the deployment of
                    landing craft, the progress of the Italian campaign, aid to the guerrillas in
                    the Balkans, the relation of operations in the Mediterranean to the date of
                        <gloss target="#t_Overlord1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Overlord</hi>
                    </gloss>, and coordination of the command of strategic air operations. <persName
                        corresp="#p_CC2">Churchill</persName> discussed the same subjects on the
                    following day at the meeting of the Combined Chiefs of Staff with <persName
                        corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> and himself, <hi rend="italic"
                        >post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_331">p. 331</ref>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
